♪ What is called
a fate-destined calamity ♪

104
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:54,070
♪ Is merely human's obsession ♪

105
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:52,720
I want two of these.

106
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:53,720
Give it to me.

107
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:59,360
♪ Let the waves rise in layers,
to be crossed ♪

108
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:02,740
♪ Crashing through day and night ♪

109
00:09:04,180 --> 00:09:09,180
♪ Yet they cannot wash away
that year's moon ♪

110
00:09:10,650 --> 00:09:11,640
♪ If you ask what destiny truly means ♪

111
00:09:12,190 --> 00:09:13,460
♪ It is heroism, it is regret ♪

112
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:16,200
♪ It is separation, never to meet again ♪

113
00:09:17,550 --> 00:09:19,650
♪ In the end, it is simply the fortune
of having a confidant at your side ♪

114
00:09:20,590 --> 00:09:23,090
♪ Passing through endless years,
no words needed ♪

115
00:09:24,010 --> 00:09:30,600
♪ As long as we once had it,
even if it vanishes in an instant ♪

116
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:32,710
Miss, please buy one.

117
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:36,940
♪ It is still worth it ♪

118
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:33,630
Take it.

119
00:09:33,630 --> 00:09:34,320
Thank you.

120
00:09:35,670 --> 00:09:36,530
This is not bad.

121
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,170
Keep it well.

122
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:47,010
See?

123
00:09:47,630 --> 00:09:49,630
-Thank you, miss.
-Thank you, miss.

124
00:09:53,130 --> 00:09:56,540
♪ What is called
a fate-destined calamity ♪

125
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:03,700
♪ Is merely human's obsession ♪

126
00:10:05,690 --> 00:10:09,020
♪ Let the waves rise in layers,
to be crossed ♪

127
00:10:09,740 --> 00:10:12,460
♪ Crashing through day and night ♪

128
00:10:10,390 --> 00:10:11,890
Why did everyone leave?

129
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:13,500
I booked the whole place.

130
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:17,050
We haven't even entered Bailejing yet,

131
00:10:17,050 --> 00:10:19,620
