134
00:10:22,390 --> 00:10:23,990
Can't you let me die happily?

135
00:10:24,030 --> 00:10:25,430
I raised you for nothing.

136
00:10:26,410 --> 00:10:28,220
Here comes the rice noodles.

137
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,500
Here. Enjoy.

138
00:10:29,980 --> 00:10:30,580
Sir.

139
00:10:31,820 --> 00:10:32,420
What is it?

140
00:10:32,790 --> 00:10:34,230
I want to ask you about something.

141
00:10:34,230 --> 00:10:35,090
Ask something?

142
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:35,630
Sure.

143
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:36,940
One piece of information,

144
00:10:36,940 --> 00:10:37,870
one copper coin.

145
00:10:39,510 --> 00:10:40,240
Copper coin.

146
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,230
Is it enough?

147
00:10:48,050 --> 00:10:49,620
Just ask whatever you want.

148
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:51,160
How far is it to Bailejing?

149
00:10:51,220 --> 00:10:51,790
Well...

150
00:10:53,010 --> 00:10:54,320
You shouldn't go there.

151
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,450
Shouldn't go there?

152
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:58,740
I'll give you two. Is it enough?

153
00:10:58,740 --> 00:10:59,360
Well...

154
00:11:03,820 --> 00:11:04,280
Take it.

155
00:11:05,390 --> 00:11:05,990
Thank you.

156
00:11:06,550 --> 00:11:07,250
You guys

157
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:08,810
need to cross a mountain.

158
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,390
But after that,

159
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:12,480
no one has ever made it farther.

160
00:11:12,670 --> 00:11:13,410
Why?

161
00:11:13,820 --> 00:11:14,930
Because these years,

162
00:11:14,930 --> 00:11:15,860
a gang of bandits

163
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:18,600
has been entrenched
at the entrance to Bailejing.

164
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:20,290
Whoever wants to enter Bailejing

165
00:11:20,290 --> 00:11:22,120
must pass through them.

166
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:25,150
And they are very scary.

167
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:27,170
They specialize in robbing outsiders.

168
00:11:27,170 --> 00:11:29,230
They never leave anyone alive.

169
00:11:29,510 --> 00:11:30,840
Since they never leave anyone alive,

170
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:32,060
how did you know it?

171
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,090
Just guessing.

172
00:11:34,220 --> 00:11:35,290
Enjoy your meal.

173
00:11:37,290 --> 00:11:38,550
What are you planning?

174
00:11:39,270 --> 00:11:40,730
We are out of money anyway.

175
00:11:40,870 --> 00:11:41,960
Let's go make some money from the bandits

176
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:43,160
and enter Bailejing.

177
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:48,050
Since we are entering the bandit's lair,

178
00:11:48,050 --> 00:11:50,050
it's better to disguise ourselves.

179
00:11:56,410 --> 00:11:57,030
Mentor.

180
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:58,080
You just added hair extensions.

181
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,700
What kind of disguise is this?

182
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:00,960
None of your business.

183
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,410
What are you looking at?

184
00:13:36,170 --> 00:13:37,010
Nothing.

185
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:38,530
I just washed my hands.

186
00:13:57,550 --> 00:13:58,550
Phoenix Inn?

187
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:09,460
Come on! Drink up!

188
00:14:09,460 --> 00:14:10,260
Bring it over!

189
00:14:10,300 --> 00:14:11,100
Bring it over!

190
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:12,000
-Great!
-Delicious!

191
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,700
Where did this lady come from?

192
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:15,750
The best tables here

193
00:14:15,890 --> 00:14:17,290
have already been booked by us.

194
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:17,960
However!

195
00:14:18,670 --> 00:14:20,660
You can sit on my lap!

196
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:21,330
Come on!

197
00:14:21,350 --> 00:14:22,710
Come drink with me!

198
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:24,870
Sir, let me sit on your lap, will you?

199
00:14:24,870 --> 00:14:26,100
Go away! Go away!

200
00:14:26,130 --> 00:14:27,030
Sit on my lap!

201
00:14:27,030 --> 00:14:28,080
Drink with me.

202
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:29,080
Don't cause trouble.

203
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:29,680
Good wine!

204
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:30,860
Drink up!

205
00:14:30,860 --> 00:14:31,430
Come on!

206
00:14:31,450 --> 00:14:31,720
Drink up!

207
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:32,390
-Let's drink.
-Let's drink.

208
00:14:32,390 --> 00:14:33,250
Come, drink up.

209
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,060
Take a look. Who are the bandits here?

210
00:14:39,510 --> 00:14:40,550
This is good wine.

211
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:43,320
Come on.

212
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:43,790
Bottoms up!

213
00:14:43,790 --> 00:14:44,340
Drink more!

214
00:14:44,340 --> 00:14:45,040
Really?

215
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,010
That's amazing!

216
00:14:50,940 --> 00:14:52,270
These are all outsiders

217
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:53,410
eager to make money.

218
00:14:55,850 --> 00:14:58,340
Please have some tea.

219
00:15:02,620 --> 00:15:03,240
Enjoy.

220
00:15:06,220 --> 00:15:07,240
This is a bandit inn.

221
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:08,640
The waiters are bandits.

222
00:15:08,820 --> 00:15:10,030
They will probably strike soon.

223
00:15:10,030 --> 00:15:10,790
Excuse me!

224
00:15:11,270 --> 00:15:12,330
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

225
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:14,100
Yes?

226
00:15:17,030 --> 00:15:18,770
Don't we need a token to enter Bailejing?

227
00:15:18,770 --> 00:15:20,630
When are you selling us the token?

228
00:15:20,870 --> 00:15:21,290
Yeah!

229
00:15:21,290 --> 00:15:23,020
When will you give us the token?

230
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:26,320
Our Phoenix Inn

231
00:15:26,340 --> 00:15:28,410
will auction
the token of Bailejing shortly.

232
00:15:28,410 --> 00:15:30,670
Please be patient, everyone.

233
00:15:30,750 --> 00:15:31,810
Alright, alright.

234
00:15:32,210 --> 00:15:34,140
We need a token to enter Bailejing?

235
00:15:34,250 --> 00:15:39,020
Bailejing is the stronghold
of Mount Shiwan.

236
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:40,310
There are many treasures inside

237
00:15:40,310 --> 00:15:42,530
that have never been seen outside.

238
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:44,940
If you have the ability to bring them out,

239
00:15:44,940 --> 00:15:47,250
any of them can make you rich overnight.

240
00:15:47,890 --> 00:15:51,020
Everyone here
wants to go to Bailejing for the treasure.

241
00:15:51,550 --> 00:15:52,920
Then what is this token?

242
00:15:53,030 --> 00:15:53,930
Bailejing

243
00:15:53,980 --> 00:15:56,100
is just like a palace
where the emperors used to live.

244
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:58,250
No matter how capable you are
or how high your rank is,

245
00:15:58,250 --> 00:15:59,580
without this pass token,

246
00:15:59,580 --> 00:16:01,220
you will be stopped at the palace gate.

247
00:16:01,220 --> 00:16:01,820
Then why is this token

248
00:16:01,820 --> 00:16:03,410
not being kept by Bailejing itself,

249
00:16:03,410 --> 00:16:05,010
but here in your Phoenix Inn?

250
00:16:05,110 --> 00:16:06,870
Our boss got this token.

251
00:16:07,010 --> 00:16:09,340
We had the advantage
of a favorable position.

252
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:10,910
You two are also going to Bailejing,
right?

253
00:16:10,910 --> 00:16:11,440
Yes.

254
00:16:11,460 --> 00:16:12,750
Do you want to join the auction?

255
00:16:12,750 --> 00:16:14,950
You just need to pay a registration fee.

256
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,130
We need to pay for it?

257
00:16:18,050 --> 00:16:19,030
Miss.

258
00:16:19,940 --> 00:16:21,450
Your man is useless.

259
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:23,580
He doesn't even have this much money.

260
00:16:23,580 --> 00:16:25,350
Why don't you be with me?

261
00:16:25,510 --> 00:16:26,650
I'll pay the registration fee

262
00:16:26,650 --> 00:16:28,070
for you.

263
00:16:32,610 --> 00:16:33,240
Boss!

264
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:41,690
These guys

265
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:42,860
are really useless.

266
00:16:42,860 --> 00:16:43,360
Exactly.

267
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,700
Didn't you just

268
00:16:44,820 --> 00:16:46,420
tell me not to cause trouble?

269
00:16:47,170 --> 00:16:48,170
I said that to you.

270
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:50,210
But I only have 2 months to live.

271
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:58,680
It's for the auction.

272
00:16:58,730 --> 00:16:59,400
Two people.

273
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:02,680
Everyone, everyone.

274
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:04,089
Calm down, please.

275
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,940
Our manager

276
00:17:06,250 --> 00:17:07,140
is treating you

277
00:17:07,380 --> 00:17:09,430
to good wine and dishes.

278
00:17:09,940 --> 00:17:12,750
We wish everyone here

279
00:17:12,829 --> 00:17:14,760
good luck and great fortune in Bailejing.

280
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:16,569
We wish you great wealth.

281
00:17:16,849 --> 00:17:17,250
Come on.

282
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:18,109
Hurry up.

283
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:20,240
Zhu! Check with the kitchen.

284
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,500
Bring over the wine! Hurry!

285
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:22,240
Come on!

286
00:17:22,940 --> 00:17:23,380
Come on!

287
00:17:23,380 --> 00:17:23,790
Cheers!

288
00:17:23,790 --> 00:17:24,790
Come on. Drink up.

289
00:17:25,069 --> 00:17:25,480
Come on, cheers.

290
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:26,010
Let's drink on our own.

291
00:17:26,010 --> 00:17:26,720
Here!

292
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:30,790
These are all signature dishes of our inn.

293
00:17:30,790 --> 00:17:32,600
Come! Cheers!

294
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:12,220
As long as they are dead.

295
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:13,220
If you chop them into pieces,

296
00:18:13,220 --> 00:18:14,810
how can I send them to Bailejing?

297
00:18:14,810 --> 00:18:15,940
Let's do it as usual.

298
00:18:16,210 --> 00:18:18,940
Keep the good-looking ones
and present them to the Chief,

299
00:18:18,940 --> 00:18:19,940
and the ugly ones—

300
00:18:20,050 --> 00:18:20,660
kill them.

301
00:18:21,090 --> 00:18:21,610
Got it.

302
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:29,870
This one is good-looking.

303
00:18:29,870 --> 00:18:31,090
Let's keep him and take him away.

304
00:18:31,090 --> 00:18:31,740
That woman—

305
00:18:31,740 --> 00:18:32,420
Kill her.

306
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,240
Who are you?

307
00:18:55,530 --> 00:18:56,480
Robbers.

308
00:18:57,700 --> 00:18:58,760
Give me your money.

309
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,680
So we are in the same business.

310
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:02,740
Please show mercy.

311
00:19:02,830 --> 00:19:04,010
I have no money.

312
00:19:04,100 --> 00:19:04,870
All my money

313
00:19:05,050 --> 00:19:06,590
is with the Chief.

314
00:19:08,050 --> 00:19:08,680
We...

315
00:19:09,380 --> 00:19:10,720
We have no money.

316
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:13,480
Where is the Chief?

317
00:19:20,870 --> 00:19:23,040
[Zhongshan Fortress]

318
00:19:27,290 --> 00:19:28,830
According to the rules of the fortress,

319
00:19:28,830 --> 00:19:29,960
when I blow the horn,

320
00:19:30,270 --> 00:19:32,200
they come out to receive the goods.

321
00:20:02,590 --> 00:20:04,220
This man looks pretty good.

322
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:05,670
Carry him away and change his clothes.

323
00:20:05,590 --> 00:20:09,580
[Zhongshan Fortress]

324
00:20:05,690 --> 00:20:07,020
The rest, the old place.

325
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:28,940
You are the Chief?

326
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:30,940
Disgusting!

327
00:22:06,610 --> 00:22:10,370
[Feng Huang, Head of Phoenix Fortress]

328
00:22:33,220 --> 00:22:35,090
This man is in good shape.

329
00:22:35,790 --> 00:22:37,090
I like him very much.

330
00:22:38,110 --> 00:22:39,910
Chief, this guy is a good fighter

331
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:40,980
of unknown origin.

332
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,510
We don't know what he's up to.

333
00:22:42,510 --> 00:22:43,710
It's safer to kill him

334
00:22:43,750 --> 00:22:44,950
to avoid any trouble.

335
00:22:46,590 --> 00:22:48,650
Do you think I can't handle this brat?

336
00:22:48,750 --> 00:22:49,290
No.

337
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:51,680
I just think he doesn't deserve you.

338
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,500
He's so handsome.

339
00:22:57,010 --> 00:22:58,480
I think we're a good match.

340
00:23:04,370 --> 00:23:05,970
I don't think you deserve me.

341
00:23:06,740 --> 00:23:07,720
I'll kill you!

342
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:08,590
Get out!

343
00:23:18,030 --> 00:23:19,110
How arrogant.

344
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:20,480
I like it.

345
00:23:20,770 --> 00:23:21,900
I like conquering.

346
00:23:23,460 --> 00:23:25,180
This is our first time meeting. Isn't...

347
00:23:25,180 --> 00:23:26,900
Isn't this moving a bit too fast?

348
00:23:26,900 --> 00:23:28,830
I actually prefer being reserved.

349
00:23:29,770 --> 00:23:30,920
Wait, wait!

350
00:23:31,220 --> 00:23:31,830
Chief.

351
00:23:32,130 --> 00:23:32,890
We can't.

352
00:23:35,140 --> 00:23:36,070
What do you mean?

353
00:23:36,350 --> 00:23:37,050
I mean,

354
00:23:37,660 --> 00:23:39,220
I'm like a corpse right now.

355
00:23:39,350 --> 00:23:39,980
I can't move.

356
00:23:39,980 --> 00:23:40,720
It's no fun.

357
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:43,010
Fulfill one wish for me,

358
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:44,560
and you can have me.

359
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:46,250
I promise to blow your mind.

360
00:23:48,330 --> 00:23:49,070
What wish?

361
00:23:49,540 --> 00:23:51,270
I actually already have a wife.

362
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:53,490
She is seriously ill and dying.

363
00:23:54,070 --> 00:23:56,470
But she heard Bailejing is very beautiful.

364
00:23:56,680 --> 00:23:58,740
So she wants to see it before she dies.

365
00:23:59,550 --> 00:24:01,710
Chief, your token—

366
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:03,220
could you lend it to me?

367
00:24:03,890 --> 00:24:05,480
I'll let her go there and see it,

368
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:06,720
so I can fulfill her wish.

369
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:08,120
Once I bury her properly,

370
00:24:08,550 --> 00:24:11,080
I'll come back
and have babies with you, okay?

371
00:24:14,180 --> 00:24:16,110
You're quite an affectionate man.

372
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:17,960
I can give you the token

373
00:24:18,380 --> 00:24:20,640
so your wife can go to Bailejing herself.

374
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:23,330
But you have to stay.

375
00:24:28,140 --> 00:24:29,800
Actually, it's my first time.

376
00:24:30,330 --> 00:24:31,460
Who are you kidding?

377
00:24:34,700 --> 00:24:37,590
This drug can knock out 3 tigers
for 12 hours.

378
00:24:37,830 --> 00:24:39,700
Yet you broke free
in just 10 minutes.

379
00:24:39,700 --> 00:24:40,820
You're amazing.

380
00:24:41,030 --> 00:24:42,430
I like you so much!

381
00:24:51,070 --> 00:24:51,730
Who are you?

382
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:53,030
That is my wife.

383
00:24:54,220 --> 00:24:56,420
Didn't you say she was dying of illness?

384
00:24:56,420 --> 00:24:57,820
She has a mental illness.

385
00:24:59,420 --> 00:25:00,040
The token!

386
00:25:00,940 --> 00:25:01,420
Move!

387
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:04,590
This woman.

388
00:25:38,310 --> 00:25:39,040
The token...

389
00:25:57,830 --> 00:25:59,160
Thank you for saving me.

390
00:26:23,900 --> 00:26:24,360
Come on.

391
00:26:28,070 --> 00:26:29,070
You saved my life.

392
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:30,400
So you are the savior of me

393
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:32,260
and the entire Phoenix Fortress.

394
00:26:32,380 --> 00:26:34,090
Since I've decided to be your friend,

395
00:26:34,090 --> 00:26:34,790
from now on,

396
00:26:35,030 --> 00:26:36,530
I'll make sure the whole fortress

397
00:26:36,530 --> 00:26:37,400
turns over

398
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:38,440
a new leaf.

399
00:26:38,660 --> 00:26:39,920
We won't disgrace you.

400
00:26:40,900 --> 00:26:42,330
As for our past misunderstandings,

401
00:26:42,330 --> 00:26:43,730
they are all in this wine.

402
00:26:43,830 --> 00:26:45,330
Let's bury the hatchet.

403
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:46,010
Alright.

404
00:26:47,730 --> 00:26:49,390
Miss, what's your name?

405
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:53,170
You're like a completely different person
from during the day.

406
00:26:53,900 --> 00:26:55,500
You speak Chinese very well.

407
00:26:55,550 --> 00:26:56,750
I'm also Han Chinese.

408
00:26:56,920 --> 00:26:59,290
I came here from Bailejing
with my dad when I was 13,

409
00:26:59,290 --> 00:27:01,160
became the Chief at 17,

410
00:27:01,570 --> 00:27:02,700
and I'm 22 this year.

411
00:27:04,500 --> 00:27:05,500
What's your name?

412
00:27:05,510 --> 00:27:06,370
How old are you?

413
00:27:06,420 --> 00:27:08,050
Who's older between us?

414
00:27:08,790 --> 00:27:10,920
Zhang Haiqi. I'm from the south.

415
00:27:11,980 --> 00:27:13,110
As for my age...

416
00:27:13,830 --> 00:27:15,160
I'm much older than you.

417
00:27:15,220 --> 00:27:17,280
Then I'll call you Sister from now on.

418
00:27:17,550 --> 00:27:18,080
Alright.

419
00:27:20,610 --> 00:27:21,940
Everyone, stop eating!

420
00:27:22,050 --> 00:27:23,000
Hold on a second.

421
00:27:23,500 --> 00:27:24,570
From today,

422
00:27:25,180 --> 00:27:26,380
she is my sister.

423
00:27:26,550 --> 00:27:27,660
You will treat her

424
00:27:27,770 --> 00:27:28,900
just as you treat me.

425
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:31,100
A toast to my sister first.

426
00:27:32,090 --> 00:27:32,590
Come on.

427
00:27:35,500 --> 00:27:36,750
To the Chief!

428
00:27:36,750 --> 00:27:37,510
Chief!

429
00:27:43,750 --> 00:27:44,980
His name is Zhang Hailou.

430
00:27:44,980 --> 00:27:46,290
He is my apprentice.

431
00:27:46,850 --> 00:27:48,440
Sorry for offending you today.

432
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:49,240
A toast to you.

433
00:27:49,420 --> 00:27:49,950
Alright.

434
00:27:53,700 --> 00:27:54,430
We got to know

435
00:27:55,460 --> 00:27:57,120
each other through fighting.

436
00:27:57,240 --> 00:27:58,140
May this wine

437
00:27:58,660 --> 00:27:59,200
wash away

438
00:28:00,660 --> 00:28:01,390
our grudges.

439
00:28:03,330 --> 00:28:05,250
I never said I wanted to wash them away.

440
00:28:05,250 --> 00:28:06,160
I want us...

441
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:08,640
to be tangled up forever.

442
00:28:20,030 --> 00:28:20,940
Try this.

443
00:28:21,070 --> 00:28:21,640
Let's go.

444
00:28:25,770 --> 00:28:26,310
Hero.

445
00:28:28,700 --> 00:28:29,630
This is my son.

446
00:28:29,750 --> 00:28:30,380
He is 18.

447
00:28:31,510 --> 00:28:32,160
Hero,

448
00:28:32,250 --> 00:28:34,460
thank you for letting us go.

449
00:28:34,980 --> 00:28:36,940
Your martial skills are really amazing.

450
00:28:36,940 --> 00:28:38,740
Can I be your apprentice?

451
00:28:38,900 --> 00:28:41,960
This young man looks like
he's made for martial arts.

452
00:28:42,030 --> 00:28:44,490
Are you interested
in joining our Archives?

453
00:28:45,380 --> 00:28:46,700
Kneel.

454
00:28:46,830 --> 00:28:48,450
Mentor, you are right!

455
00:28:48,840 --> 00:28:49,930
Get up. Get up.

456
00:28:49,960 --> 00:28:50,640
Come on.

457
00:28:50,670 --> 00:28:51,730
Let's have a drink.

458
00:28:52,180 --> 00:28:53,980
I will take him as my apprentice.

459
00:28:54,350 --> 00:28:55,220
We're so happy.

460
00:28:57,470 --> 00:28:59,990
Mentor, enjoy your drink.

461
00:29:00,700 --> 00:29:01,770
Eat first.

462
00:29:01,950 --> 00:29:02,770
Come.

463
00:29:03,610 --> 00:29:04,770
My son has a mentor now.

464
00:29:04,770 --> 00:29:06,830
Come on, let's have a drink together.

465
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:08,680
Zhang Hailou.

466
00:29:09,610 --> 00:29:11,560
Our engagement is always valid.

467
00:29:11,650 --> 00:29:14,450
If you want to fulfill it,
you are welcome anytime.

468
00:29:14,850 --> 00:29:15,680
Engagement?

469
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:20,740
Just forget it.

470
00:29:22,570 --> 00:29:23,310
Chief,

471
00:29:24,050 --> 00:29:26,180
you actually deserve someone better.

472
00:29:50,220 --> 00:29:51,420
I'll help you woo her.

473
00:29:54,660 --> 00:29:55,660
You'll help me...

474
00:29:59,110 --> 00:30:00,150
Sister, try this.

475
00:30:00,180 --> 00:30:01,110
It's delicious.

476
00:30:05,080 --> 00:30:05,610
Come on.

477
00:30:07,870 --> 00:30:09,130
For this kind of thing,

478
00:30:09,380 --> 00:30:10,840
I have a lot of experience.

479
00:30:11,770 --> 00:30:13,280
It takes skill.

480
00:30:13,940 --> 00:30:15,200
I'll tell you in detail later.

481
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:16,530
You are still too young.

482
00:30:19,700 --> 00:30:21,750
Did you come to Nanqiang

483
00:30:22,330 --> 00:30:24,380
for sightseeing or business?

484
00:30:25,360 --> 00:30:26,820
We are going to Bailejing.

485
00:30:28,940 --> 00:30:30,870
You really are going to Bailejing?

486
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:40,290
No, it's too dangerous there.

487
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:41,820
You can't go.

488
00:30:41,900 --> 00:30:44,030
What's so dangerous about Bailejing?

489
00:30:47,790 --> 00:30:49,450
I'll take you to see something

490
00:30:49,940 --> 00:30:51,400
that came from Bailejing.

491
00:31:14,480 --> 00:31:15,140
We're here.

492
00:31:22,720 --> 00:31:24,920
This talisman is used for suppression.

493
00:31:25,790 --> 00:31:26,680
What's inside?

494
00:31:27,180 --> 00:31:28,270
Have you noticed

495
00:31:28,750 --> 00:31:30,280
how quiet it is around here?

496
00:31:32,070 --> 00:31:32,810
It really is.

497
00:31:33,270 --> 00:31:34,050
This forest is dense,

498
00:31:34,050 --> 00:31:35,380
and the air here is damp.

499
00:31:35,740 --> 00:31:37,070
In theory, there should be a lot of

500
00:31:37,070 --> 00:31:38,650
snakes, bugs, rats, and ants.

501
00:31:38,650 --> 00:31:41,180
But it's gotten much quieter
since we came in.

502
00:31:41,740 --> 00:31:43,500
Ever since this coffin was placed here,

503
00:31:43,500 --> 00:31:45,830
all the animals nearby have disappeared.

504
00:31:46,090 --> 00:31:49,010
They seem to be very afraid of
what's inside the coffin.

505
00:31:49,010 --> 00:31:51,140
Animals have a much faster ability
to sense danger

506
00:31:51,140 --> 00:31:52,440
than humans do.

507
00:31:54,720 --> 00:31:56,120
After all this build-up,

508
00:31:56,270 --> 00:31:57,870
let's open it and take a look.

509
00:32:05,980 --> 00:32:08,240
Are the people here a bit superstitious?

510
00:32:08,250 --> 00:32:11,450
Dying in red clothes
won't turn you into a vengeful ghost.

511
00:32:13,770 --> 00:32:14,570
Give me a hand.

512
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:34,710
Who is this person?

513
00:32:35,500 --> 00:32:36,700
What happened to her?

514
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:37,700
Her name is Wanduo.

515
00:32:37,700 --> 00:32:38,960
She is from Bailejing.

516
00:32:39,460 --> 00:32:41,120
I used to do business with her.

517
00:32:41,420 --> 00:32:42,250
A month ago,

518
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:44,350
she suddenly said she was getting married,

519
00:32:44,350 --> 00:32:45,440
but on the day of the wedding,

520
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:46,830
she escaped from Bailejing.

521
00:32:46,830 --> 00:32:48,700
She wasn't dead yet
when I was trying to save her.

522
00:32:48,700 --> 00:32:50,500
The last thing she said to me was,

523
00:32:51,770 --> 00:32:53,220
"Never go to Bailejing."

524
00:32:59,180 --> 00:33:00,940
We have a custom
of keeping the coffin here.

525
00:33:00,940 --> 00:33:02,250
Those who die unexpectedly

526
00:33:02,250 --> 00:33:05,110
must be kept above ground
for 49 days before burial.

527
00:33:05,270 --> 00:33:06,670
That's why I put her here.

528
00:33:10,770 --> 00:33:12,370
What happened to Bailejing?

529
00:33:13,960 --> 00:33:14,690
I don't know.

530
00:33:15,500 --> 00:33:17,640
I only do business
with people coming out of Bailejing.

531
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:18,530
I rarely go in.

532
00:33:24,640 --> 00:33:27,180
You trade corpses with Bailejing
for tokens?

533
00:33:28,140 --> 00:33:30,240
Why does Bailejing need so many corpses?

534
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:31,070
I have no idea.

535
00:33:31,570 --> 00:33:33,400
The rule of trading corpses for tokens

536
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:35,130
only started in recent months.

537
00:33:35,250 --> 00:33:35,900
Moreover,

538
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:38,720
at first, picked-up corpses
were acceptable.

539
00:33:38,720 --> 00:33:39,920
But in recent months,

540
00:33:40,030 --> 00:33:42,430
their demand for corpses has been growing.

541
00:33:43,590 --> 00:33:46,190
Killing living people
is also acceptable now.

542
00:33:46,460 --> 00:33:47,480
Are there any tokens left?

543
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:48,940
All the people I sent to Bailejing

544
00:33:48,940 --> 00:33:49,880
never returned.

545
00:33:50,270 --> 00:33:52,070
Why do you still want to go there?

546
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:53,770
My mentor is sick.

547
00:33:53,770 --> 00:33:54,960
I have to cure her.

548
00:33:58,350 --> 00:33:59,180
Sister,

549
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:04,180
you're late.

550
00:34:04,790 --> 00:34:06,270
The last 10 tokens of this year

551
00:34:06,270 --> 00:34:08,000
have all been sold to a caravan,

552
00:34:08,210 --> 00:34:10,230
to a man named Jiutou Yandai.

553
00:34:10,610 --> 00:34:11,840
This afternoon, the caravan

554
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:13,510
has already set off for Bailejing.

555
00:34:13,510 --> 00:34:14,760
If you want to go there,

556
00:34:14,760 --> 00:34:16,190
you can only ask the caravan for them.

557
00:34:16,190 --> 00:34:16,900
Otherwise,

558
00:34:19,190 --> 00:34:21,190
you'll have to wait until next year.

559
00:34:22,860 --> 00:34:24,280
Then prepare a horse for me.

560
00:34:24,280 --> 00:34:25,900
As long as they haven't entered Bailejing,

561
00:34:25,900 --> 00:34:27,830
I'll have a way to get close to them.

562
00:34:27,960 --> 00:34:28,760
Hurry, hurry.

563
00:34:28,860 --> 00:34:29,010
Yes.

564
00:34:29,010 --> 00:34:29,650
Tie it tighter.

565
00:34:29,650 --> 00:34:30,190
Alright.

566
00:34:30,670 --> 00:34:32,980
You really have to rely on friends
when you're away from home.

567
00:34:32,980 --> 00:34:33,639
Feng Huang,

568
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:35,760
you are much more reliable than

569
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:37,360
our relative in Changxiang.

570
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:39,380
Just put it in that pocket.

571
00:34:40,340 --> 00:34:41,840
It's because I became friends

572
00:34:41,840 --> 00:34:43,170
with you today, Sister.

573
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:44,420
That's enough.

574
00:34:44,420 --> 00:34:45,650
Tell them to stop packing.

575
00:34:45,650 --> 00:34:46,820
These things are too cumbersome.

576
00:34:46,820 --> 00:34:48,340
Just pick one or two of them.

577
00:34:48,340 --> 00:34:49,739
A dying person like me

578
00:34:49,980 --> 00:34:51,179
can't use all of them.

579
00:34:51,650 --> 00:34:53,780
Sister, what are you talking about?

580
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:55,480
You must live on

581
00:34:55,510 --> 00:34:56,280
and get well.

582
00:34:56,630 --> 00:34:58,440
Bailejing is a magical place.

583
00:34:58,460 --> 00:34:59,110
Your illness

584
00:34:59,110 --> 00:35:00,910
will definitely be cured there.

585
00:35:01,030 --> 00:35:02,210
And your apprentice

586
00:35:02,420 --> 00:35:04,420
seems to be quite worried about you.

587
00:35:05,210 --> 00:35:06,190
He is still young

588
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:09,280
and hasn't experienced
the loss of loved ones yet.

589
00:35:09,630 --> 00:35:11,830
He'll be fine after experiencing more.

590
00:35:13,010 --> 00:35:14,130
But if I die,

591
00:35:16,190 --> 00:35:17,590
he will be left all alone.

592
00:35:18,690 --> 00:35:19,150
Mentor,

593
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:20,410
are you leaving so soon?

594
00:35:20,410 --> 00:35:21,460
I'll be waiting for you here.

595
00:35:21,460 --> 00:35:22,170
When you come back,

596
00:35:22,170 --> 00:35:23,570
take me to that Archives.

597
00:35:28,030 --> 00:35:29,510
Here, take this.

598
00:35:30,880 --> 00:35:31,860
When I come back,

599
00:35:32,590 --> 00:35:33,450
I'll teach you.

600
00:35:33,820 --> 00:35:36,220
I'll go have your grandmaster cured first.

601
00:35:36,710 --> 00:35:37,310
Take care.

602
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:38,460
Thank you, Mentor.

603
00:35:42,090 --> 00:35:42,400
Well.

604
00:35:42,400 --> 00:35:43,300
This doesn't look bad.

605
00:35:43,300 --> 00:35:43,800
Come on.

606
00:35:45,030 --> 00:35:45,860
It must be worth a lot of money.

607
00:35:45,860 --> 00:35:46,480
Of course.

608
00:35:46,480 --> 00:35:47,070
Bro,

609
00:35:47,960 --> 00:35:49,620
if you're not good with words,

610
00:35:50,010 --> 00:35:51,210
you can say less.

611
00:35:51,610 --> 00:35:53,940
Charm her with things you're good at.

612
00:35:54,440 --> 00:35:56,300
Look, you always wear too little.

613
00:35:56,590 --> 00:35:57,980
How do I charm her?

614
00:35:58,400 --> 00:35:59,670
How?

615
00:36:03,590 --> 00:36:04,530
If you're good at singing,

616
00:36:04,530 --> 00:36:05,460
sing some songs.

617
00:36:05,940 --> 00:36:06,870
Some love songs.

618
00:36:09,630 --> 00:36:12,230
Just wait patiently
for your mentor to return.

619
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:27,280
The clear mountain
breeze brushes over you.

620
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:29,570
I miss you again and again in my heart.

621
00:36:29,570 --> 00:36:31,630
If I'm in your heart,

622
00:36:31,940 --> 00:36:34,460
I'll follow you to the ends of the earth.

623
00:37:22,710 --> 00:37:23,880
Adjutant Zhang.

624
00:37:25,500 --> 00:37:29,600
Can you feel the strange spiritual energy

625
00:37:29,670 --> 00:37:31,670
in this southern forest?

626
00:37:32,470 --> 00:37:33,460
I am dull

627
00:37:34,420 --> 00:37:35,880
and haven't perceived it.

628
00:37:43,530 --> 00:37:44,300
Commander.

629
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:45,940
We found an inn ahead.

630
00:37:46,070 --> 00:37:47,800
It's the only way to Bailejing.

631
00:37:47,960 --> 00:37:50,210
We should be able
to find some news about Bailejing.

632
00:37:50,210 --> 00:37:51,420
Adjutant Zhang,

633
00:37:51,460 --> 00:37:53,280
go ahead and check it out.

634
00:37:58,360 --> 00:37:59,210
Yes.

